Class CoreStreamUtils

java.lang.Object
org.krmdemo.techlabs.core.utils.CoreStreamUtils
public class CoreStreamUtils extends Object
Utility-class that provides methods to transform the stream or var-args-arrays of values into linked or sorted sets and stream or var-args-arrays of entries into linked or sorted map. An enumeration MergeFunction could be used to handle the entries with the same key.

    • sortedMap

      @SafeVarargs public static <K extends Comparable<K>, V> NavigableMap<K,V> sortedMap(Map.Entry<K,V>... entriesArr)
      Transform the var-args-arrays of entries into the sorted map, where the entries with the same key are merged with the default merge-function MergeFunction.OVERWRITE.
      In order to avoid NullPointerException all invalid entries are filtered out, where the filter is based on using entryIsValid(Map.Entry) function.
      Type Parameters:
      K - the type of key
      V - the type of value
      Parameters:
      entriesArr - var-args-arrays of entries
      Returns:
      the sorted map, which is collected from those entries, as NavigableMap,
